news.title: Jaipur: Amrit Kunj owners get plots in new scheme after 12 years
news.para: The Jaipur Development Authority (JDA) has allotted plots to successful allottees in another scheme named Amirt Kunj-2 in zone-12.

news.title: Homes delivered but no power connection: Vipul World buyers
news.para: DHBVN stopped providing new electricity connections to 16 societies in July last year for non-payment of charges for developing power infrastructure by developers. DHBVN had to recover Rs 317 crore from the developers of these colonies.

news.title: Promoters' stake in Aurum PropTech rises to 50.34% post rights-issue
news.para: “This fresh infusion of capital will further institutionalise adoption of technology in the real estate sector,” said Ashish Deora, Founder and Chief Executive Officer of Aurum Ventures, the holding company of Aurum PropTech.

news.title: Phoenix Mills to add 4.4 million sq ft to retail portfolio in 12-15 months
news.para: Phoenix that counts Singapore sovereign wealth fund GIC and the Canada Pension Plan Investment Board (CPPIB) as its partners will hold around 4.4 million sq ft cumulative leasable retail space across the four malls. The company is investing around Rs 4,000 crore to develop the retail component of these projects.

news.title: Phoenix Mills' net profit jumps 101%, income up 28% in FY22
news.para: Operating profit for the quarter rose 39% to Rs 241 crore and Rs 734 crore for the financial year, up 49%.

news.title: Noida sets up high-level panel to frame structural audit policy for highrises
news.para: In fact, the three authorities - Noida, YEIDA and GNIDA - had earlier passed a resolution at their respective board meetings to form the joint committee for framing norms of the structural audit policy, a first of its kind in the state.

news.title: Supertech insolvency: NCLAT asks IRP to file status report
news.para: "List this Appeal on 01.06.2022. Let IRP also file Status Report by the next date. In the meantime, Interim order to continue," said a three- member NCLAT bench headed by Chairperson Justice Ashok Bhushan.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers' profit up 28% at Rs 27 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 380.99 crore in the fourth quarter of 2021-22 fiscal year from Rs 302.38 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: HeidelbergCement to cut emissions by nearly 50% by 2030
news.para: The company will use recycled materials and carbon capture to reduce CO2 emissions to 400 kilograms per tonne, down from a previous target of 500 kilograms, highlighting its efforts to cut emission in the cement production, which is among the most polluting industrial processes.

news.title: Nagpur civic body finds 287 structures unsafe, orders demolition
news.para: As per the survey, highest number of dilapidated buildings are in Gandhibagh zone, followed by Mangalwari (50), Dhantoli (49 ) and Dharampeth (46). Laxmi Nagar zone failed to submit the latest report.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of Golden Life Agro India, Sunshine Agro Infra on Jun 16
news.para: The properties put on the block include land parcels and a double storied building situated across West Bengal, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in a notice.

news.title: Holcim takes a $5 billion currency cover against Adani deal receivables
news.para: These derivative bets, said to be of shorter maturities, will cover the exchange rate risk on more than $5 billion as and when the acquisition is completed after all approvals are obtained.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP mulls issuing guidelines on reviewing & constructing basements
news.para: However, as a first step, now BBMP is asking all the buildings with basements to have a water pumpset. This pumpset is needed to flush out the water stored during rains.

news.title: Civic bodies in West Bengal plan property tax re-evaluation
news.para: “The tax structure of the areas under different civic bodies has not been revised for years. We have told the valuation board to visit all municipalities to come up with a real valuation of the property tax structure in tune with the present land price of the areas," said Firhad Hakim.

news.title: About 11 illegal Pilibhit colonies given one month notice before demolition
news.para: These colonies are being developed along national highways 730 and 731, Pilibhit-Madhotanda road and Pilibhit-Bilgawan road adjoining the city municipal area limits.
